[[File:Defense.gov photo essay 091007-N-0696M-300.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Black in December 2009]]
'''Lewis Niles Black''' (born August 30, 1948) is an [[Americans|American]] comedian, author, [[playwright]], social critic, and actor. He is known for his [[Comedy Central]] series ''[[Lewis Black's Root of All Evils]]''. He made a regular appearance on ''[[The Daily Show]] with [[Jon Stewart]]''. 

Black was born in [[Silver Spring, Maryland|Silver Spring]], [[Maryland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/11/Lewis-Black.html |title=Lewis Black Biography (1948â€“) |publisher=Filmreference.com |date= |accessdate=2010-11-01}}</ref>

